@node "Usage" "Usage"

@{b} USAGE:@{ub}

    Use it just like the original Execute Command supplied with Scalos!
    
    The CLI image at the far right will spawn a new Shell if clicked.  Also the image on the left will do the same should you feel the urge to click on that ;o)
    
    The command to be executed can have a user defined STACK value by adjusting the number in the string gadget bottom centre.  The default for Workbench is 4096 but MUI applications require at least 8192.  UNIX ported programs will usually require much higher values.

    Enter just a directory path, device name or assign and the window will be opened on the desktop for you to browse.

    It you wish to enter a web URL you @{b}must@{ub} use the 'http://' prefix.  To load a local file depends on what browser you have configured in the OpenURL preferences program.  Voyager uses 'http:///Work:WWW/index.html' for example - notice the @{b}3@{ub} slashes.  It is also case sensitive for file names.  IBrowse uses 'http://localhost/Work:www/index.html' and doesn't seem to mind about case in the file name. 

    You may drag an entry from the history pop-up list into the command string gadget it it feels better for you.  Otherwise double click on an entry in the history list and it will be placed in the command string ready to be edited or executed.

    Filename completion is achieved by pressing RAMIGA + TAB when in the command string gadget.  Pressing this combination multiple times cycles through all possible matches.

    If when starting the module you get Enforcer hits, PLEASE make sure you have the latest versions of the mentioned MUI custom classes.  It is known that old versions of TransferAnim.mcc cause a large number of hits.
@endnode


@node "Configure" "Configuring"

@{b} CONFIGURING:@{ub}

    You may alter what is executed when pressing the 'CLI' button by changing the NEWCLI environment variable.  At install time you can change this from the default if required.  For instance you may use 'WShell' or something similar available on Aminet.  The default (should you overwrite it) is: "NewShell WINDOW=CON:0/20/600/200/ScalosShell/AUTO/WAIT"
    
    Additionally if you want to use the URL facility make sure you configure the correct browser in the seperate OpenURL preference program which is supplied with the library.

@endnode

